liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A dominant start for the USA. They've had 62 per cent of the possession in that half, with six shots (two on target) to the Swede's two, none on target. Incredibly, the USA have had 15 touches in Sweden's box, but as things stand, they still can't find the breakthrough. Half time has come at just the right time for the Swedish team who just have not been able to get into the game at all. They have had half the number of passes that the USA have and they have not even really been able to use the small amount of possession they have had effectively. It was 0-0 in two of Sweden's three group stage matches as well, but this feels very, very different and they are, frankly, hanging on.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Half time: Sweden 0-0 USA

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: We've spoken about Sweden's heading ability, but it was Lindsey Horan who has rattled the crossbar with a towering header from the corner. Keeper Zećira Mušović was well beaten by the pace of the header, and has now gone down after her acrobatic effort at a save. We'll keep an eye on that because although she's played on now, she does not look comfortable and grimaced as she kicked it clear.
